      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Rebuilding Alliance excels in directing resources to the front lines of crisis. Its 2023 financial data shows that <cite id=\"3\">$825,817 in contributions</cite> supported large-scale relief, including <cite id=\"5\">$2.5 million in hot meals program expenses</cite> and food parcels, often facilitated through significant non-cash contributions. This operational model allows for <cite id=\"12\">direct service delivery</cite> in high-conflict zones. Furthermore, the organization is governed by a <cite id=\"13\">7-member board</cite> that ensures all activities align with its mission of <cite id=\"14\">realizing a just and enduring peace</cite> founded upon equal rights."
      ],
      "summary": "founded in 2003, Rebuilding Alliance is a U.S.-based non-profit dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">advancing equal rights for Palestinians</cite> through a dual approach of grassroots advocacy and direct humanitarian relief. The organization maintains a significant presence in the <cite id=\"2\">Gaza Strip, West Bank, and Jerusalem</cite>, focusing on community preservation and emergency response. In 2023, the organization reported <cite id=\"3\">Total Revenue of $825,817</cite>, reflecting its role as a specialized humanitarian actor. A hallmark of its operations is a <cite id=\"4\">90.3% program expense ratio</cite>, ensuring that every dollar of public contribution is directed toward its core missions, which include <cite id=\"5\">hot meal distribution and food parcel grants</cite>. Beyond direct aid, Rebuilding Alliance engages in <cite id=\"6\">leadership learning missions and advocacy</cite> to help Palestinian families maintain their land and homes. The charity has achieved a <cite id=\"7\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, the highest level of disclosure, and operates with <cite id=\"8\">90.3% independent board members</cite> to ensure robust oversight of its international programs.",
